==English==
===Etymology===
From {{L.}} '''[[immensurabilis]]''', from prefix '''[[im-]]''', ''not'', variant form of '''[[in-]]''', plus '''[[mensura]]''', ''measure'', plus suffix '''[[-abilis]]''', ''able''

===Adjective===
'''immensurable'''

# [[unmeasurable]], [[immeasurable]]; not able to be measured, therefore connoting extremely large

